<h1>Welcome to FilterExample App</h1>
<p>This page demonstrates the usage of action filters in ASP.NET MVC.</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>LogActionFilter:</strong> Records the name of each action method and the time of access in <em>ActionLog.txt</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>UniqueUserFilter:</strong> Counts unique users based on their IP address and records the count in <em>UniqueUsersCount.txt</em>.</li>
</ul>

<p>Check the <em>ActionLog.txt</em> and <em>UniqueUsersCount.txt</em> files in the project root to see the logged data.</p>
